one quick way to update the repo with powershell:


git add .; git commit -m "Update"; git push


it will stage the changes then commit with the message (mandatory) "Update" and it will push it to the server


in mac or linux just use '&&' instead of ';'

therefore (mac and linux)

git add . && git commit -m "Update" && git push

You can also create a script and invoke it everytime
